Mozambique Aims at 100 Percent Polio Vaccination
LUANDA , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- Mozambique is aiming at a 100 percent vaccination rate among the country 's three million children under five years of age in its second nationwide vaccination campaign designed from September 28 to October 2.
A Health Ministry official said here Monday that about 97 percent of the targeted children were vaccinated against polio last month when the country launched its first polio vaccination drive , Noticias daily reported Monday .
Fixed posts and mobile brigades have been planned for the second vaccination campaign throughout the country , which aims to kick out polio in the country by 2000 , the paper said .
The latest three polio cases in the country were reported in 1993 .
